00036     std::string
00037     callback_name(const std::string& name, const std::string& type,
00038                   int size)
00039     {
00040       std::string res = name;

00049     void
00050     RemoteUGenericCallbackImpl::initialize(UGenericCallback* owner, bool)
00051     {
00052       owner_ = owner;
00053       std::string type = owner_->type;
00054       //owner_->name =
00055       // callback_name(owner_->name, owner_->type, owner_->nbparam);
00056       GD_FINFO("Registering %s %s %s into %s from %s",
00057                type,
00058                owner_->name,
00059                owner_->nbparam,
00060                owner_->name,
00061                owner_->objname);
00062       UClient& cl = *dynamic_cast<RemoteUContextImpl*>(owner_->ctx_)->client_;
00063       if (type == "var")
00064         URBI_SEND_PIPED_COMMAND_C
00065           (cl,
00066            libport::format("external %s %s from %s",
00067                            type, owner_->name, owner_->objname));
00068       else if (type == "event" || type == "function")
00069         URBI_SEND_PIPED_COMMAND_C
00070           (cl,
00071            libport::format("external %s (%s) %s from %s",
00072                            type, owner_->nbparam, owner_->name,
00073                            owner_->objname));
00074       else if (type == "varaccess")
00075         echo("Warning: NotifyAccess facility is not available for modules in "
00076              "remote mode.\n");
00077     }

00096     void
00097     RemoteUGenericCallbackImpl::registerCallback()
00098     {
00099       RemoteUContextImpl* ctx = static_cast<RemoteUContextImpl*>(owner_->ctx_);
00100       GD_FINFO("Pushing %s in %s", owner_->name, owner_->type);
00101       UTable& t =
00102         dynamic_cast<RemoteUContextImpl*>(owner_->ctx_)
00103         ->tableByName(owner_->type);
00104       t[callback_name(owner_->name, owner_->type, owner_->nbparam)]
00105         .push_back(owner_);
00106       if (owner_->target)
00107       {
00108         static_cast<RemoteUVarImpl*>(owner_->target->impl_)
00109           ->callbacks_.push_back(this);
00110         std::string targetname = owner_->target->get_name();
00111         // Register the UVar to be updated if it's not there.
00112         std::list<UVar*> &us = ctx->varmap()[targetname];
00113         if (!libport::has(us, owner_->target))
00114           us.push_back(owner_->target);
00115       }
00116     }
